1) Stock Price Data (for returns, heatmap, S0)
Source:

✔ Yahoo Finance via yfinance API

Used for:

intraday prices (5 days, 30m interval)

daily prices (1 year)

real-time-ish current spot price

historical price series

2) Option Chain Data (strikes, expiry, lastPrice)
Source:

✔ Yahoo Finance option chain feed via yfinance

Used for:

strike prices

call/put option type

current market option price

expiration dates

3) Risk-Free Rate
Currently:

✔ Hard-coded: r = 0.05

But could be changed to:

US Treasury 1-month yield

Fed Funds rate

SOFR

or auto-fetch from FRED API

4) Volatility & drift estimation
Source:

✔ Computed by YOU from daily historical price data:

µ annualized = mean return × 252

σ annualized = std.dev × sqrt(252)

These are derived values, not externally provided.
